of <b>Thibierge</b> (and, in North America, an altered form of this), which is of the same origin as <b>Théberge</b> (see   Theberge  ). The surname <i>Thivierge</i> is very rare in France. Compare   Verge  .","History: Hippolyte Thibierge from Blois in Loir-et-Cher, France, married Renée Hervet in Blois in 1653, died in Sainte-Famille, Île d'Orléans, QC, in 1700. His descendants also bear another altered form of the surname, <i>Verge</i>."]},{"name":"Verges","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Spanish Raul, Carmelita, Gilberto, Jorge, Jose, Juanita, Lourdes, Nieves, Rafael, Ricardo, Vidal.  French Emile.","French (Occitan; <b>Vergès</b>) and Catalan (<b>Vergés</b>): from the plural of Occitan <i>verg(i)èr</i> and Catalan <i>verger</i> ‘orchard’, a topographic name for someone who lived near an orchard or garden, or an occupational name for someone who was employed in one (see   Verge   3 and   Verdier   2)."]}]},{"name":"Jean","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Like   Jane   and   Joan  , a medieval variant of Old French <i>Je(h)anne</i>. Towards the end of the Middle Ages this form became largely confined to Scotland. In the 20th century it became more widely used in the English-speaking world and enjoyed a period of great popularity, but it is now out of fashion. Among numerous well-known and influential bearers are the British novelists  Jean Plaidy  (  Eleanor Hibbert ,  1910–93 ) and  Jean Rhys  (  Ella Gwendolen Rees Williams ,  1894–1979 ), British actress  Jean Simmons  (  1929–2010 ), and American-born actress  Jean Seberg  (  1938–79 ). It is also found as a variant spelling of the masculine name   Gene ."],"variants":[{"name":"John","meanings":["As a boy's name this represents a revival of Middle English <i>Jan</i>, a by‐form of   John  , or an adoption of the common European form with this spelling. As a girl's name it is a short form of names such as   Janet   and   Janice ."]},{"name":"Jeane","meanings":["Variant spelling of   Jean ."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"When Jean de Vergy I was born about 1248, in Europe, his father, Henri de Vergy I, was 34 and his mother, Beatrix de Ferrette, was 25. He married marguerite DE NOYERS, in 1263. They were the parents of at least 3 sons and 1 daughter. He died about 1310, at the age of 64."},"et":{"ABT 1248–ABT 1310":"umbes 1248–umbes 1310","1248–1272":"1248–1272","1248–1310":"1248–1310","1258–Male":"1258–Surnud","1250–1310":"1250–1310","1267–1312":"1267–1312","1270–1335":"1270–1335","1305–1360":"1305–1360","–Male":"Surnud","1215–1263":"1215–1263","1225–1287":"1225–1287","1263":"1263","ABT 1248":"umbes 1248","1360":"1360","1250":"1250","1272":"1272","1270":"1270","1305":"1305","1215":"1215","1248":"1248","1225":"1225","1335":"1335","1258":"1258","about 1305":"umbes 1305","1312":"1312","1267":"1267","BEF 1287":"enne 1287","ABT 1310":"umbes 1310","1310":"1310","1243":"1243","1287":"1287","Til-Châtel, Côte-d'Or, Bourgogne, France":"Til-Châtel, Côte-d'Or, Bourgogne, Prantsusmaa","Fay, Orne, Normandie, France":"Fay, Orne, Normandie, Prantsusmaa","Europa":"Europe"},"fi":{"ABT 1248–ABT 1310":"noin 1248–noin 1310","1248–1272":"1248–1272","1248–1310":"1248–1310","1258–Male":"1258–Kuollut","1250–1310":"1250–1310","1267–1312":"1267–1312","1270–1335":"1270–1335","1305–1360":"1305–1360","–Male":"Kuollut","1215–1263":"1215–1263","1225–1287":"1225–1287","1263":"1263","ABT 1248":"noin 1248","1360":"1360","1250":"1250","1272":"1272","1270":"1270","1305":"1305","1215":"1215","1248":"1248","1225":"1225","1335":"1335","1258":"1258","about 1305":"noin 1305","1312":"1312","1267":"1267","BEF 1287":"ennen vuotta 1287","ABT 1310":"noin 1310","1310":"1310","1243":"1243","1287":"1287","Til-Châtel, Côte-d'Or, Bourgogne, France":"Til-Châtel, Côte-d'Or, Bourgogne, Ranska","Fay, Orne, Normandie, France":"Fay, Orne, Normandie, Ranska","Europa":"Europe"},"fr":{"ABT 1248–ABT 1310":"environ 1248–environ 1310","1248–1272"